reviews.title: "A champagne pub"
reviews.text:
What the best pubs in London are to beer, this one is to champagne.
Warm atmosphere and good flat prots like French tapas. 
Place at the foot of the most expensive avenue in the world, whether in the evening or during the day, it is a pleasure.

reviews.title: Excessive and unjustified prices!!!
reviews.text:
While walking along the magnificent Avenue de Champagne, we came across this wine bar, a bit by chance and we wanted to try it...
The interior is quite nice...on the other hand, the glass of champagne at 15 Euros is really unjustified...especially since the day before, we were in the same type of establishment, in Epernay and there, it was 7.50 Euros, the cut...
In short, a real tourist trap...Result, once...and that will be enough...

reviews.title: Went there for dinner and
reviews.text: Went there for dinner and it was amazing. Booked a table the day before and even this was a nice experience. The owner was so friendly and told us that there are only tapas to be served. Didn’t know what to expect and ordered five different ones. The waitress told us it could be too much but..... the Food was very delicious and we fought ourselves to finish all of it! Highly recommendable!!!!! Was our best experience with dinner in Epernay!!!!!

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

This two-day Florence itinerary is organized by location and backed by Tripadvisor reviews and ratings to make sure every step counts. You’ll see iconic attractions and have plenty of time for gelato, pasta, and wine.

articleContent.title: Where centuries-old traditions continue to inspire

seoInfo.metaDescription: A visit to Japan is incomplete without experiencing the Kansai region. Regarded as the country’s cultural heart, it’s home to cities like the ever-popular Kyoto and the towering culinary hub of Osaka—this year’s World Expo host.

articleContent.title: Celebrate the best of Osaka’s food and nightlife with Suntory

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’ve ever found yourself standing in line for hours at a famous ramen spot in Japan, you’d probably agree that food and drinks are a big part of why we travel. It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. Share a drink with locals, friends, and fellow travelers, and experience the camaraderie, stories, and traditions that make up the heart of a destination, forging deeper connections along the way.

tripContent.title: 11 stops that prove Louisville is a cultural hub
tripContent.description: Louisville is brimming with rich history, art of all kinds, and architecture that's not to be missed. Check out these must-stop cultural attractions in Kentucky's biggest city.

articleContent.title: How to spend a weekend in LA's Hollywood

seoInfo.metaDescription: Spend time exploring Hollywood's rich history, vintage glamour, and star power.

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide
tripContent.description: "Our family loves going to Orlando—and not just for the theme parks. Yes, we enjoy getting to ride rollercoasters and be transported to another world, but spending time in a colorful, diverse city and the surrounding nature is delightful. We live just over an hour from Orlando, so when we feel the need for good city vibes and to feel welcome in a neighborhood besides our own, Orlando is a fantastic option for us." - Rob Taylor, 2TravelDads.com

review.title: "Un pub de champagne"
review.text:
Ce que les meilleurs pubs de Londres sont à la bière, celui-ci est au champagne.
Ambiance chaleureuse et bonne prots plats genre tapas à la française. 
Place au pied de l'avenue la plus chère du monde, que ce soit le soir ou dans la journée, c'est un plaisir.
